					<![CDATA[
						 <p>This feels unclear in some area's.</p> <p>Are the D-class just reliving the an-artists memories with their own childhood setting as the theme and characters?</p> <p>Or is the painting simply warping their memory to make it seem as though they experienced the artists trauma?</p> <p>That aside, it's an alright article, but the exposure sessions seem just one too many for the article.</p> <p>No-vote for now.</p> 
				 	]]>
